 Note that Delete is only available for Draft orders."},{"id":"so4","text":"You've shipped 50 out of 100 units on a sales order line. What status does the order show?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Shipped — any shipment changes the status"},{"id":"b","text":"In Production — the order stays in production until all units ship"},{"id":"c","text":"Partially Shipped — some lines have shipped quantities but not all are fully fulfilled","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"Draft — partial shipments don't affect status"}],"explanation":"When some but not all line items are fully shipped, the order shows Partially Shipped (yellow chip). Each line independently tracks its shipped quantity vs. ordered quantity. The order moves to Shipped only when all lines are fully fulfilled."},{"id":"so5","text":"In the sales order detail view, you notice a line item's shipped quantity is shown in green. What does this mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The line item is on backorder"},{"id":"b","text":"The line item has been fully shipped — shipped quantity equals or exceeds ordered quantity","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The line item's shipment is in transit"},{"id":"d","text":"The line item has been invoiced"}],"explanation":"Green text on the shipped quantity means the line is fully shipped (isFullyShipped = true). Yellow text means partially shipped (some shipped but not all). This color coding gives you a quick visual status of fulfillment per line."},{"id":"so6","text":"When adding a line item to a new sales order, where do parts come from?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"You type in a free-text part description — no part catalog lookup"},{"id":"b","text":"An autocomplete searches the Parts Catalog, showing only Active parts by part number and description","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"You select from a dropdown of all parts regardless of status"},{"id":"d","text":"Parts are automatically pulled from the linked quote"}],"explanation":"The line item part field is an autocomplete that searches only Active parts from the Parts Catalog. It shows results in 'Part # — Description' format. You must select a part from the search results."},{"id":"so7","text":"Where can you see how a sales order connects to its source quote?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"In the Sales Orders table — there's a Quote column showing the link"},{"id":"b","text":"In the detail view's info grid — the Quote field shows the quote number as a clickable entity link","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Quotes and sales orders are not linked in the system"},{"id":"d","text":"Only in the Reports module under Order Traceability"}],"explanation":"The sales order detail view shows the linked quote number in the info grid. The quote number is a clickable entity link that opens the quote detail dialog, giving you full traceability from quote to order."},{"id":"so8","text":"You want to find all orders for a specific customer that haven't shipped yet. How do you filter the list?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Use the Search field to type the customer name and manually scan for non-shipped statuses"},{"id":"b","text":"Set the Customer filter to the specific customer, then set the Status filter to Draft, Confirmed, or In Production"},{"id":"c","text":"Go to the customer's detail page and check their Orders tab"},{"id":"d","text":"Both B and C would work","isCorrect":true}],"explanation":"The sales orders list page has both Customer and Status filters. Select the customer from the dropdown and then filter by status. You could also navigate to the customer's detail page and check their Orders tab for a customer-centric view."},{"id":"so9","text":"What happens to the financial summary when you change the tax rate on a sales order?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Nothing changes until you save — totals are calculated server-side"},{"id":"b","text":"The Tax amount and Total update in real time as you type the new rate","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"You must click a Recalculate button to update the totals"},{"id":"d","text":"Tax is calculated per line item, not at the order level"}],"explanation":"The summary section in the create/edit dialog computes subtotal, tax amount (subtotal x rate%), and grand total in real time using computed signals. Changes to the tax rate or line items are reflected immediately."},{"id":"so10","text":"A Draft sales order can be deleted, but a Confirmed order cannot. Why?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Confirmed orders have been communicated to the customer — deletion would break the audit trail. Cancellation preserves the record.","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"There is no difference — both can be deleted"},{"id":"c","text":"Confirmed orders are locked by the accounting system"},{"id":"d","text":"It's a bug — confirmed orders should also be deletable"}],"explanation":"Draft orders haven't been committed, so deletion is safe. Confirmed orders represent a business commitment — deleting them would break the audit trail. Instead, you cancel a confirmed order, which preserves the record with a Cancelled status for history and traceability."},{"id":"so11","text":"How does the create dialog for a sales order differ from a simple form dialog?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It uses a standard single-column form layout like other create dialogs"},{"id":"b","text":"It uses a split layout — line items table and add-line form on the left, order details and summary on the right sidebar","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It opens as a full-page view instead of a dialog"},{"id":"d","text":"It has a multi-step wizard with separate pages for details and lines"}],"explanation":"The SO create dialog uses a 1100px split layout. The left (main) panel contains the line items table and the add-line form with part autocomplete, quantity, and unit price. The right sidebar has order details (customer, PO, credit terms, delivery date, tax rate), notes, and a live summary showing subtotal, tax, and total."},{"id":"so12","text":"You click a sales order row in the table. What happens to the URL?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Nothing — the detail opens as a popup with no URL change"},{"id":"b","text":"The URL updates to include ?detail=sales-order:{id}, making the view shareable and bookmarkable","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The page navigates to /sales-orders/{id} as a separate route"},{"id":"d","text":"The URL changes to /sales-orders?selected={id}"}],"explanation":"Clicking a row opens the detail dialog via DetailDialogService, which updates the URL to include ?detail=sales-order:{id}. This means you can copy the URL and share it — anyone opening it will land on the same sales order detail. The URL is cleared when the dialog closes."}]}"""
