        // ── Detail Workspace (Article) ───────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "The Sales Order Detail Workspace",
            Slug = "sales-orders-detail-workspace",
            Summary = "Tour the eight tabs of the sales order detail panel — Overview, Lines, Schedule, Shipments, Returns, Documents, Invoices, and Activity — and learn what each one shows and the warning badges that flag attention.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 5,
            AppRoutes = """["/sales-orders"]""",
            Tags = """["sales-orders","sales","detail","tabs"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## The Sales Order Detail Workspace\n\nClicking any row in the Sales Orders list opens the **detail panel** — a tabbed workspace that holds everything about that order in one place. The URL updates to `?detail=sales-order:{id}` so the view is bookmarkable and shareable. The panel header shows the order number and the customer name (a clickable link to the customer record), with a close (X) button on the right.\n\nBelow the header is an **eight-tab bar**. Some tabs show a small count badge, and several show a yellow warning triangle when they need attention. Here is what each tab does.\n\n### 1. Overview\n\nThe default tab. It shows:\n- **Status / info grid** — the status chip plus Customer PO, linked Quote (clickable), Credit Terms, Requested Delivery date, and Confirmed date. Fields only appear when they have a value.\n- **Edit Details button (Draft only)** — opens an inline form to set Customer PO, Credit Terms, and Requested Delivery date. This is the only place to populate those header fields after a quote→order conversion. See *Editing a Draft Sales Order*.\n- **Fulfillment summary** — three at-a-glance stats: lines with jobs, lines shipped, and shipment count.\n- **Totals grid** — Subtotal, Tax (with the rate %), and the bold grand Total.\n- **Notes**, a scannable **barcode**, and **Created / Updated** timestamps.\n- **Action buttons** — Confirm (Draft only), Cancel Order (Draft or Confirmed), and Delete (Draft only). Destructive actions sit on the left, the primary Confirm on the right.\n\n### 2. Lines\n\nThe line-item table: line number, part number (clickable when linked), description, quantity, a combined **Shipped / Remaining** column (shipped is green when fully shipped, yellow when partial), unit price, and line total. On a **Draft** order this tab gains Add / Edit / Delete controls. When a line has jobs, an expander reveals each job's number, stage, assignee, priority, and due date. The tab shows a **count badge** of the number of lines and a **warning triangle** when one or more non-Draft lines have no job yet.\n\n### 3. Schedule\n\nA per-line milestone timeline (order → production → ship) with a visual timeline bar and milestone cards marked Done, Overdue, or Upcoming. A line whose milestones are slipping is flagged **At Risk**, and the tab shows a warning triangle when any line is at risk. The data loads the first time you open the tab.\n\n### 4. Shipments\n\nOne card per shipment, each linking to the shipment record and showing carrier, tracking number, shipped/delivered dates, shipping cost, and weight, plus nested tables of shipment lines and packages. A **count badge** shows the number of shipments; a **warning triangle** appears when the order is partially shipped (lines still have remaining quantity).\n\n### 5. Returns\n\nOne card per customer return (RMA) tied to this order — return number, status, reason, return date, and links to the original and rework jobs. A **warning triangle** appears when any return is still open (not Closed).\n\n### 6. Documents\n\nUpload, download, and delete files attached to the order — drawings, customer POs, packing instructions, and CAD files (`.pdf`, images, Office docs, `.step`, `.stl`, `.dxf`, and more, up to 50 MB each). Each file shows a type icon, size, and upload date. A **count badge** shows how many documents are attached. See *Editing a Draft Sales Order* for how the rest of the order is changed.\n\n### 7. Invoices\n\nA rollup of every invoice generated from this order's shipments. Each card links to the invoice and shows amount, due date, payment status, and which shipments it covers. A summary at the bottom compares **Total Invoiced** against the **Order Total**. A **warning triangle** appears when there are shipped-but-not-yet-invoiced shipments — your cue to bill the customer.\n\n### 8. Activity\n\nThe chronological audit timeline for the order: confirmations, cancellations, line edits, header changes, and inline comments — every state change is recorded here.\n\n### Reading the warning badges\n\nThe tab warnings are a quick triage tool:\n- **Lines** triangle → a confirmed line has no production job yet.\n- **Schedule** triangle → a line is at risk of missing its dates.\n- **Shipments** triangle → the order is only partially shipped.\n- **Returns** triangle → an open RMA needs resolution.\n- **Invoices** triangle → a shipment has gone out but hasn't been invoiced.\n\nScan the tab bar first: the badges tell you where the order needs attention before you open a single tab.","sections":[]}"""
        });

