            AppRoutes = """["/sales-orders"]""",
            Tags = """["sales-orders","sales","draft","editing"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Editing a Draft Sales Order\n\nA sales order is fully editable while it is in **Draft** status. Once you Confirm it, the line table and header become read-only (the order is now a commitment to the customer). This article covers everything you can change on a Draft from the detail panel.\n\n### Editing line items (Lines tab)\n\nOpen the order, go to the **Lines** tab. On a Draft, the tab shows an **Add Line** button and each row gains Edit and Delete icons.\n\n**Add a line:**\n1. Click **Add Line**. An inline form appears below the table.\n2. Use the **part picker** to search the Parts Catalog by part number or name and select a part. (A line can also be a lump-sum / ad-hoc line with no part — leave the picker empty and just fill the description.)\n3. The **Description** auto-fills from the part name; you can override it.\n4. Enter **Quantity** (fractional quantities up to four decimals are allowed) and **Unit Price**.\n5. Click **Save**. The line is appended and the totals recompute.\n\n**Edit a line:** Click the pencil icon on a row. The inline form opens pre-filled. Note that the **part link is fixed at add time** — editing lets you change the description, quantity, and unit price, but not the part itself. To change the part, delete the line and add a new one.\n\n**Delete a line:** Click the trash icon. A confirmation dialog appears. (A Draft order must keep at least one line.)\n\nEvery add / edit / delete returns the refreshed order, so the Subtotal, Tax, and Total update immediately.\n\n### Price-list auto-fill\n\nWhen you pick a catalog part on a line, the system looks up the **customer's price list** for that part. If an applicable price-list entry exists, the line's **Unit Price is filled in automatically** with the customer-specific price. If no price resolves, the field is left blank for you to enter manually. This keeps customer-negotiated pricing consistent without manual lookup — but you can always override the auto-filled price before saving.\n\n### Editing the header (Overview tab)\n\nThree order-header fields can be edited on a Draft from the **Overview** tab: **Customer PO**, **Credit Terms**, and **Requested Delivery Date**.\n\n1. On the Overview tab, click **Edit Details**.\n2. An inline form opens with the three fields.\n3. Update any of them and click **Save**.\n\nThis edit path exists specifically because an order created by converting a quote starts with these fields empty — and the Overview only displays header fields that have a value, so without Edit Details there would be no way to populate them post-conversion. Use it to record the customer's PO number, set payment terms, and lock in the delivery date before you confirm.\n\n### What you can't edit, and when\n\n- **Tax rate** is set in the create dialog. Header editing covers PO / terms / delivery only.\n- **Customer** is fixed at creation — it determines billing context and the applicable price list.\n- **After Confirm**, the Lines tab and the Edit Details button disappear. Lines, header, and totals are locked. If a confirmed order is wrong, cancel it (which preserves the audit trail) and create a corrected order rather than editing in place.\n\n### Drafts are auto-saved\n\nWhile you're filling out the **create** dialog (before the order is first saved), the form auto-saves to your browser so an accidental reload or logout doesn't lose your work — you'll be offered to recover it. This is separate from the order's Draft status: the create-dialog draft is local recovery; the order's Draft status is its server-side lifecycle state.","sections":[]}"""
