            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/sales-orders"]""",
            Tags = """["sales-orders","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Schedule Tab — At-Risk Milestones\n\nThe **Schedule** tab (`ScheduleTimelineComponent`) turns each order line into a three-milestone timeline: order date -> production -> ship. Each milestone is rendered as Done, Overdue, or Upcoming. A line is flagged **At Risk** when the server sets `isAtRisk = true` on its milestone data -- its target dates are slipping. When a line is at risk, past (non-`deliveryDate`) milestones render as **Overdue** rather than merely Done.\n\n- `scheduleAtRiskCount` counts the at-risk lines; when it is > 0 the tab bar shows the yellow `tab__warning` triangle (tooltip key `salesOrders.tabWarning.atRisk`).\n- Schedule data is lazy-loaded the first time the tab is opened, not on initial detail load.\n- At-risk is a derived, read-only signal -- there is no control to manually mark a line at risk; resolve it by moving the underlying jobs forward.\n\n## Returns Tab — RMA Links\n\nThe **Returns** tab lists every customer return (RMA) tied to this order, one card each (`SalesOrderReturn` model). Each card carries up to two job links and surfaces an open-return warning.\n\n- **Original job** -- `originalJobId` / `originalJobNumber`: the job that produced the returned goods (null when not linked).\n- **Rework job** -- `reworkJobId` / `reworkJobNumber`: the job auto-created to rework/replace the return (null until rework is initiated).\n- Either link is omitted when its id is null; both open the linked job.\n- The tab shows the `tab__warning` triangle when any return is still open (status not Closed).\n\n## Fractional Quantity & 4-Decimal Pricing\n\nSales-order line **quantity and unit price are `decimal(18,4)`** on the server -- UoM-aware shops need fractional quantities (e.g. 2.5 kg, 0.75 hr). All three line forms enforce this consistently:\n\n- **Quantity** -- `Validators.min(0.0001)`; the input uses `step=\"0.0001\" min=\"0.0001\"`. Zero and negative are rejected; the smallest valid quantity is `0.0001`.\n- **Unit price** -- `step=\"0.0001\" min=\"0\"`; price may be `0` but not negative.\n- This applies in the create dialog (`so-dialog`), the in-place line editor on the detail panel, and the recurring-order dialog.\n- Display trims trailing zeros (via `DecimalPipe`) so whole numbers still read as whole numbers.\n\n## Draft Auto-Save & Resume\n\nThe **create dialog** auto-saves the in-progress order to the browser so an accidental reload or logout never loses work (`draftConfig` / `DraftConfig`, persisted to **IndexedDB**). On reopening the dialog you are offered to recover the draft.\n\n- This is **local recovery for the create form only** -- it is distinct from the order's server-side **Draft** lifecycle status. The form draft exists before the order is ever saved; the Draft *status* is the saved order's first lifecycle state.\n- Recovery is offered on page reload and on next login from the same browser.\n\n## Why the Detail-Line Table Is Read-Only After Draft\n\nA sales order is fully editable only while its status is **Draft**. The detail panel exposes Add / Edit / Delete line controls and the **Edit Details** header form **only** when the order is Draft (`editingLineId` and the inline line form are gated on Draft status).\n\n- Once the order is **Confirmed**, it is a commitment to the customer; the line table, header fields, and totals are locked, and the editing affordances disappear.\n- This is intentional, not a limitation: editing a confirmed order in place would break the audit trail. To change a confirmed order, **cancel** it (which preserves the record as Cancelled) and create a corrected order.\n- Tax rate is never editable on the detail panel -- it is set in the create dialog. The customer is fixed at creation because it determines billing context and the applicable price list.","sections":[]}"""
        });

